properties.name: text
properties.value:
Hola!, I'm Violet.
I've been watching this Magikarp
because its skin holds more secrets than it seems.
This study found that fish skin microbiomes
reflect their evolutionary history
better than their gut or gills.
It's like reading a species' past
just by looking at its microbes.
[Han et al., 2024]

properties.name: text_es
properties.value:
Hola, soy Violet.
He estado observando a este Magikarp
porque su piel guarda más secretos
de los que imaginas.
Este estudio mostró que el microbioma de la piel en peces
refleja mejor su historia evolutiva
que el del intestino o las branquias.
Es como leer el pasado de una especie
solo viendo sus microbios.
[Han et al., 2024]

properties.name: text
properties.value:
We're discussing a paper
that shows how the burrower bug
doesn't get its symbionts from its parents,
but picks them up from the soil as a newborn!
And now we're wondering...
could that wild Caterpie and those Oddish nearby
be doing something similar?
Maybe they're models of environmental symbiosis too.
[Nakawaki et al., 2024]

properties.name: text_es
properties.value:
Estamos discutiendo este paper
que muestra cómo el insecto Macroscytus japonensis
no recibe sus simbiontes de sus padres,
sino que los toma del suelo al nacer.
Y ahora nos preguntamos...
¿será que ese Caterpie salvaje y esos Oddish cercanos
hacen algo parecido?
Tal vez también sean modelos de simbiosis ambiental.
[Nakawaki et al., 2024]

properties.name: text
properties.value:
Hey, I'm Hannah... You know... 
these Beedrill remind me of the beewolf wasps I read about.
They protect their babies by sealing friendly bacteria
inside waxy secretions- like a love song in hydrocarbon.
The bacteria survive even when the egg floods the nest
with deadly nitric oxide... and still manage
to shield the larvae with antibiotics.
Cool, right?
Symbiosis is survival… if you play in harmony
[Ingham et al., 2023]

properties.name: text_es
properties.value:
“¿Sabes?... estos Beedrill me recuerdan
a unas avispas llamadas beewolf que estuve leyendo.
Protegen a sus crías encerrando bacterias amigas
en una secreción cerosa—como una canción de amor en hidrocarburos.
Las bacterias sobreviven aunque el huevo inunde el nido
con óxido nítrico mortal... y aún así
protegen a la larva con antibióticos.
¿Genial, no?
La simbiosis es sobrevivir… si se toca en armonía.”
[Ingham et al., 2023]

properties.name: text
properties.value:
Bugs, fish, birds
all got microbial sidekicks!

properties.name: text
properties.value:
Some squids have glow-in-the-dark
bacteria in their bodies to make light
GET SQUID FACTS!!!

properties.name: text
properties.value: No class today… even microbes need a break!

properties.name: text
properties.value:
Symbiosis is cooperation - like revolutionary ideals
Parasitism thrives in exploitation - like capitalism.

properties.name: text_es
properties.value:
La simbiosis es cooperación - como las ideas de revolucionarias
El parasitismo vive de la explotación - como el capitalismo.

properties.name: text
properties.value: One cell swallowed another… and made mitochondria!

properties.name: text
properties.value: You're more microbe than human, Trainer!

properties.name: text
properties.value: Your gut talks to your brain - no joke!

properties.name: text
properties.value: Used to be a obligate - now it's just facultative!

properties.name: text_es
properties.value:
Profesor,
qué va a tomar en el examen?

properties.name: text
properties.value: Run to survive! That's the Red Queen's rule.

properties.name: text
properties.value:
They evolved side by side
like battle partners!

properties.name: text
properties.value: Microbes and climate are in a feedback loop!

properties.name: text
properties.value:
Ah, you're just in time.
Your next mission is a serious one.
Each student must explore a real-world case
of microbial symbiosis.
Twice, you'll stand before the guild—
once with slides, once with chalk—and present your findings.
Choose a symbiotic pair. Dive deep into the literature.
Find what makes their bond unique: nutrition? defense? evolution?
You'll have 30 minutes to make us see the invisible...
so choose wisely.

properties.name: text_es
properties.value:
Ah, justo a tiempo.
Tu próxima misión es importante.
Cada estudiante debe explorar un caso real
de simbiosis microbiana.
Harás dos presentaciones ante el gremio:
una con diapositivas, otra con la pizarra.
Elige una pareja simbiótica. Estudia a fondo la literatura.
Descubre qué hace único su vínculo: ¿nutrición? ¿defensa? ¿evolución?
Tendrás 30 minutos para hacernos ver lo invisible.
 ...elige con sabiduría.
